<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Henny+Penny&family=Poiret+One&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <title>Novelist</title>
    <style>
        body, html {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.2;
            overflow-x: hidden; /* Disable horizontal scrolling */
            overflow-y: auto;
        }

        /* Header Section */
        .header {
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            right: 0;
            background-color: white;
            color: black;
            padding: 20px 0;
            z-index: 1000;
            text-align: center;
            width: 100%%;
        }

        .henny-penny-regular {
          font-family: "Henny Penny", system-ui;
          font-weight: 400;
          font-style: normal;
        }

        .logo {
          max-width: 100px;
          max-height: 100x;
          padding: 5px 0px;
          margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .name {
            font-size: 40px;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-family: "Henny Penny", system-ui;
            padding: 20px 10px;

        }

        .poiret-one-regular {
          font-family: "Poiret One", sans-serif;
          font-weight: 400;
          font-style: normal;
        }


        /* Navigation Tabs */
        .nav {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            background-color: #444;
            padding: 10px 0;
            font-family: "Poiret One", sans-serif;
            font-weight: 100;
        }

        .nav a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 6px 10px;
            font-size: 24px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
            font-weight: 100;
            margin-right: 40px;
            margin-left: 40px;
        }

        .nav a:hover {
            background-color: #555;
        }

        /* Main Content */
        .content {
            padding-top: 0px;
            /* Removed margin-top; section margins will handle spacing */
        }

        section {
          padding: 50px;
          margin-bottom: 20px;
          padding-top: 400px;
        }

        section h2 {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-shadow: none;
        }

      #home {
        background-color: white; /* Light grey background */
      }

      #books {
        background-image: url('about-bg.jpg');
        background-size: cover;
        padding: 50px;
        color: black;
      }
      
      #about {
        background-image: url('about-bg.jpg'); /* Background image for about section */
        background-size: cover;
        padding: 50px;
        color: black;
      }
      
      #blog {
        background-color: blue; /* Green background for contact section */
        padding: 50px;
        color: black;
      }
      #contact {
        background-color: #4CAF50; /* Green background for contact section */
        padding: 50px;
        color: white;
      }

    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Header Section with Logo and Navigation -->
  <div class="header">
    <div class="logo">
      <%= image_tag 'hank.jpg', alt: 'logo', class: 'logo' %>
    </div>
    <div class="name">
        Nathan Trautenberg
    </div>
    <div class="nav">
      <a href="#home">Home</a>
      <a href="#books">Books</a>
      <a href="#about">About</a>
      <a href="#blog">Blog</a>
      <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Main Content Sections -->
  <div class="content">
    <section id="home">
        <h2 style="font-style: italic;">
        He could see the spaceship vividly, and the twelve gray aliens walking single file towards the bakery.
        The door opened, and their smiling faces and bright souls paraded on in.
        Rosaline had a mop on stand-by for the inevitable goo puddles, those little pools of happiness.
        </h2><h2>- BAKER'S DOZEN by Nathan Trautenberg</h2>
    </section>
    <section id="books">
        <h2>Books</h2>
        <p>I am currently submitting my first manuscript, BAKER'S DOZEN, to literary agents.
          It is a humorous satire about a man who struggles to do what's right for himself, even if it means letting others down.
          The story is told from multiple different characters points of views, and although a satire at heart, reads like an espionage thriller. 
        </p>
    </section>
    <section id="about">
        <h2>About</h2>
        <p>I began writing my first novel when I was sitting at a cubicle at work, bored out of my mind.
          I didn't realize I was going to write a novel, it just sort of happened.
          Boredom is a wonderful thing-- it is the impetus for creativity.
          And now I also have the plots to two more books, one screenplay, and two series worked out.
          I need more time in the day to write!
          <br><br>
          I didn't study creative writing in school, but rather philosophy and science. 
          My propensity for these subjects bleeds through my pen and colors my writing.
          While I write speculative fiction, all my themes relate to real life.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section id="blog">
        <h2>Blog</h2>
        <p>Check out our latest blog posts.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Get in touch with us through this section.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>
</html>